---
description: Prefer strict equality (=== and !==) over loose equality (== and !=)
alwaysApply: true
---

# Strict Equality

Use strict equality comparisons to avoid unexpected type coercion.

- Prefer `===` over `==`
- Prefer `!==` over `!=`

- ✅ Good:

  ```typescript
  if (status === 'active') return true
  if (count !== 0) return count
  if (value === null || value === undefined) return null
  ```

- ❌ Bad:

  ```typescript
  if (status == 'active') return true
  if (count != 0) return count
  if (value == null) return null
  ```
